= Types of Major Shirk (Shirk Akbar):


Major shirk can be divided into four types:


== 1. Shirk of Invocation . 
Evidence: The saying of Allāh, the Exalted:

#quran-block[
  فَإِذَا رَكِبُواْ فِي ٱلۡفُلۡكِ دَعَوُاْ ٱللَّهَ مُخۡلِصِينَ لَهُ ٱلدِّينَ فَلَمَّا نَجَّىٰهُمۡ إِلَى ٱلۡبَرِّ إِذَا هُمۡ يُشۡرِكُونَ ٦٥
][ And when they embark on a ship, they invoke Allāh, making their faith pure for Him; but when He delivers them to the land, behold, they associate others with Him. (Al-‘Ankabūt: Q29:65)] 

== 2. Shirk of Intention, Will, and Purpose. 
Evidence: The saying of Allāh, the Exalted:

#quran-block[
  مَن كَانَ يُرِيدُ ٱلۡحَيَوٰةَ ٱلدُّنۡيَا وَزِينَتَهَا نُوَفِّ إِلَيۡهِمۡ أَعۡمَٰلَهُمۡ فِيهَا وَهُمۡ فِيهَا لَا يُبۡخَسُونَ ١٥ أُوْلَٰٓئِكَ ٱلَّذِينَ لَيۡسَ لَهُمۡ فِي ٱلۡأٓخِرَةِ إِلَّا ٱلنَّارُۖ وَحَبِطَ مَا صَنَعُواْ فِيهَا وَبَٰطِلٞ مَّا كَانُواْ يَعۡمَلُونَ ١٦
][Whoever desires the life of this world and its
 adornment – We fully repay them for their deeds therein, and they will not be deprived. They are those for whom there is nothing in the Hereafter except the Fire, and their deeds will be nullified, and they will be in vain. (Ḥūd: Q11:15–16)]


== 3. Shirk of Obedience. 
Evidence: The saying of Allāh, the Exalted:

#quran-block[
  ٱتَّخَذُوٓاْ أَحۡبَارَهُمۡ وَرُهۡبَٰنَهُمۡ أَرۡبَابٗا مِّن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ وَٱلۡمَسِيحَ ٱبۡنَ مَرۡيَمَ وَمَآ أُمِرُوٓاْ إِلَّا لِيَعۡبُدُوٓاْ إِلَٰهٗا وَٰحِدٗاۖ لَّآ إِلَٰهَ إِلَّا هُوَۚ سُبۡحَٰنَهُۥ عَمَّا يُشۡرِكُونَ ٣١
][
They have taken their scholars and monks as lords besides Allāh, and [also] the Messiah, son of Mary. And they were not commanded except to worship one God; there is no deity except Him. Exalted is He above what they associate with Him. (At-Tawbah: Q9:31)]

Its clear interpretation (without doubt): It is obeying scholars and
     worshippers in disobedience (to Allāh), not merely calling upon them, as
     the Prophet #pbuh explained to ‘Adiyy ibn Ḥātim when he said:

     “We do not worship them.” The Prophet #pbuh replied that their worship of them  was through obedience to them in sin#footnote[When this verse was revealed, ʿAdī ibn Ḥātim #pleasedHIM — who was a Christian before embracing Islām — came to the Prophet #pbuh and said: “O Messenger of Allāh, they (the Jews and Christians) do not worship their rabbis and monks.” The Prophet #pbuh replied: “Do they not make lawful what Allāh has made unlawful, and you make it lawful? And do they not make unlawful what Allāh has made lawful, and you make it unlawful?” ʿAdī said, “Yes.” The Prophet #pbuh said: “That is their worship of them. At-Tirmidhi (Hadith no. 3370)”].

== 4. Shirk of Love. 
Evidence: The saying of Allāh, the Exalted:

#quran-block[
وَمِنَ ٱلنَّاسِ مَن يَتَّخِذُ مِن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ أَندَادٗا يُحِبُّونَهُمۡ كَحُبِّ ٱللَّهِۖ وَٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوٓاْ أَشَدُّ حُبّٗا لِّلَّهِۗ وَلَوۡ يَرَى ٱلَّذِينَ ظَلَمُوٓاْ إِذۡ يَرَوۡنَ ٱلۡعَذَابَ أَنَّ ٱلۡقُوَّةَ لِلَّهِ جَمِيعٗا وَأَنَّ ٱللَّهَ شَدِيدُ ٱلۡعَذَابِ ١٦٥
][And among people are those who take others besides Allāh as equals—they love them as they should love Allāh. But those who believe are stronger in their love for Allāh. And if only they who have wronged would consider [that] when they see the punishment, [they will be certain] that all power belongs to Allāh and that Allāh is severe in punishment. (Al-Baqarah Q2:165)]

